    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Officials Of the Washington Water\nPower company say today that work\nwill be commenced enlarging the Di-\nvision street rock cut as soon as spe-\ncial machinery is secured from the\neast. This will be ordered at once\nand will cost $4,000. The city agrees\nto pay $4,000 for the work. This 10\nconsidered about half what any pri-\nvate contractor could do the work for.\nThe Water Power company wishes\nthe rock to ballast it's tracks, which\naccounts for their low bid."
    }
